wiki.content: First single off Train's 2009 album Save Me San Francisco. According to Billboard, the song is “about a woman who's got all the right moves.” (Source Hey Soul Sister Songfacts) Written and produced by the Norwegians Espen Lind and Amund Bjørklund who also wrote/produced Beyonces monster hit “Irreplaceable” User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License and may also be available under the GNU FDL.
